Subject: ui-tui: give cursor drift prefix-walk test an explicit timeout

The cursor drift regression test walks a long realistic message across seven
terminal widths and compares every typing prefix against wrap-ansi. It is a
valid but CPU-heavy regression guard. In the full Vitest suite on this runtime,
that single case can exceed Vitest's 5s default even though it passes when run
with a longer timeout. Pin the timeout on the expensive case only.

